SUMMARY:State of AI : Context Engineering with Microsoft and Anthropic
DESCRIPTION:Modern Web (Triangle)\nContext is becoming a defining layer of modern AI systems and is shaping how models reason\, respond\, and integrate into real products. This event explores how context engineering is influencing the current state of AI and the way teams are thinking about building more capable and reliable systems.\n\n[Join us for a conversation](https://luma.com/79w48jgi) with experts from Microsoft and Anthropic as we examine emerging approaches to structuring context\, lessons from real-world AI development\, and the considerations guiding what comes next.\n\nFeaturing insights from\n[Harald Kirschner](https://www.linkedin.com/in/digitarald/)\, Principal Product Manager for GitHub Copilot and VS Code at Microsoft\n[Ado Kukic](https://www.linkedin.com/in/adocomplete/)\, Community Manager at Anthropic\n[Brandon Mathis](https://www.linkedin.com/in/mathisbrandon/)\, Engineering Lead\, This Dot Labs\n[Tracy Lee](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tracyslee/)\, CEO\, This Dot Labs\n\n[If you are interested in attending\, please RSVP using this link!](https://luma.com/iho7wvqp)
